<p><b>The Carlyle Group</b> is a global <a href="/wiki/Private_equity" title="Private equity">private equity</a> investment firm, based in <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">Washington, D.C.</a>, with more than $91.5 billion of <a href="/wiki/Equity_capital" title="Equity capital" class="mw-redirect">equity capital</a> under management.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> The firm operates four fund families, focusing on <a href="/wiki/Leveraged_buyouts" title="Leveraged buyouts" class="mw-redirect">leveraged buyouts</a>, <a href="/wiki/Growth_capital" title="Growth capital">growth capital</a>, <a href="/wiki/Real_estate" title="Real estate">real estate</a> and <a href="/wiki/Leverage_(finance)" title="Leverage (finance)">leveraged finance</a> investments. The firm employs more than 575 investment professionals in 21 countries with several offices in the <a href="/wiki/Americas" title="Americas">Americas</a>, <a href="/wiki/Europe" title="Europe">Europe</a>, <a href="/wiki/Asia" title="Asia">Asia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Australia" title="Australia">Australia</a>; its portfolio companies employ more than 415,000 people worldwide. Carlyle has over 1200 investors in 68 countries.</p>
<p>The firm has employed political figures and notable investors. Some of these figures include former <a href="/wiki/US_President" title="US President" class="mw-redirect">US President</a> <a href="/wiki/George_H._W._Bush" title="George H. W. Bush">George H. W. Bush</a> and former <a href="/wiki/US_Secretary_of_State" title="US Secretary of State" class="mw-redirect">US Secretary of State</a> <a href="/wiki/James_A._Baker_III" title="James A. Baker III" class="mw-redirect">James A. Baker III</a>. The State of <a href="/wiki/New_York" title="New York">New York</a> is currently investigating the firm in connection to an illegal kickback scheme with the state's pension fund.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
