<p><a name="Investment_focus" id="Investment_focus"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Carlyle_Group&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Investment focus">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Investment focus</span></h2>
<p>Carlyle invests primarily in the following industries: <a href="/wiki/Aerospace_engineering" title="Aerospace engineering">aerospace</a> and <a href="/wiki/Defense_contractor" title="Defense contractor">defense</a>, <a href="/wiki/Automobile" title="Automobile">automotive</a>, consumer and retail, energy and <a href="/wiki/Electric_power" title="Electric power">power</a>, <a href="/wiki/Healthcare" title="Healthcare" class="mw-redirect">health care</a>, <a href="/wiki/Real_Estate" title="Real Estate" class="mw-redirect">real estate</a>, <a href="/wiki/Quaternary_sector_of_industry" title="Quaternary sector of industry" class="mw-redirect">technology and business services</a>, <a href="/wiki/Telecommunications" title="Telecommunications" class="mw-redirect">telecommunications</a> and <a href="/wiki/Mass_media" title="Mass media">media</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Transport" title="Transport">transportation</a>. The Carlyle Group's investments are focused on <a href="/wiki/East_Asia" title="East Asia">East Asia</a>, Europe and <a href="/wiki/North_America" title="North America">North America</a>, with most investment money coming from the <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">United States</a> (65%), Europe (25%), Asia (6%), <a href="/wiki/Latin_America" title="Latin America">Latin America</a>, and the <a href="/wiki/Middle_East" title="Middle East">Middle East</a>.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since July 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup> Defense investments represent about 1% of the group's current portfolio;<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since June 2007" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup> for example, Carlyle owns 33.8% of <a href="/wiki/QinetiQ" title="QinetiQ">QinetiQ</a>,<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since July 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup> the recently <a href="/wiki/Privatized" title="Privatized" class="mw-redirect">privatized</a> <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">British</a> <a href="/wiki/Defense_contractor" title="Defense contractor">defense contractor</a>.</p>
<p><a name="History" id="History"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Carlyle_Group&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: History">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">History</span></h2>
<table class="toccolours" style="float: right; margin: 0 0 1em 1em; text-align:center; font-size: 85%;">
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="font-size: larger;">
<center><b><a href="/wiki/History_of_private_equity_and_venture_capital" title="History of private equity and venture capital">History of private equity<br />
and venture capital</a></b></center>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/wiki/File:Objectivist.jpg" class="image" title="Objectivist.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Objectivist.jpg/115px-Objectivist.jpg" width="115" height="153" border="0" /></a></td>
</tr>
